pr_title: compose: Move compose action buttons to a new popover.
pr_body:
Move the 'New topic' and 'New private message' to a popover added after the reply button.

Additional changes to the text of these buttons depending on the narrow the user is in.
Resolves  #12496 

**Update:**
Normal window:
![Screenshot from 2019-07-03 02-43-10](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/25329595/60547177-b1513a80-9d3c-11e9-8c5a-05fe9ab66a97.png)

pr_title: message_edit: Add test suite for frontend logic around message edit history.
pr_body:
Currently we only show the 'View edit history' button option if an edit has been made to the message content.
With this change, the 'View edit history' button will also be shown when only a topic edit is made.

Fixes #12320.
pr_review_comments:
[{'comment_id': 316439277, 'comment_body': "So, I think if we want to match the behavior the server would give if you received a message where edits had happened in the past, if an event has both a topic and a message edit, we should be appending a single `edit_history_event`, not two.  

So I think the correct behavior is to extract this block modifying `msg.edit_history` to a common that sits above the `topic_edit` conditional (and just copies keys from the event; there's probably a good `_` function that would do this really cleanly)", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2019, 8, 21, 23, 10, 50, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'timabbott', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 388035292, 'comment_body': "Looking at this more, I think we should (1) extract this block to a common `update_edit_history(msg, event)` that can be called once, outside the conditionals for topic or message editing, so we don't get 2 edit history events if the topic and content were edited at once (or soon, if the stream was edited too).

Does that make sense to you?", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 3, 5, 1, 42, 59, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'timabbott', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 389224119, 'comment_body': 'My bad, I thought your comment was referring to the tests. 

I made this change, but should I let the tests stay as it is? The test first edits a topic and then the content. Should I change that to make both edits simultaneously?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 3, 7, 3, 36, 54, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'vinitS101', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 424210310, 'comment_body': "I think this is fine; but ideally we'd test both simultaneous and separate.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 5, 13, 6, 53, 35, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'timabbott', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 440350811, 'comment_body': 'Here is a whitespace anomaly -- two spaces before the `=`.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 6, 15, 18, 0, 11, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'timabbott', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 440351556, 'comment_body': "I don't understand this comment.  Is it just saying the next line is what we're testing?  ", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 6, 15, 18, 1, 36, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'timabbott', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 440351813, 'comment_body': 'Another whitespace anomaly -- our style is not to have blank lines at the start of a test.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 6, 15, 18, 1, 59, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'timabbott', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 440824339, 'comment_body': 'Yeah. It was already there as part of the previous test, so I just let it be. ', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 6, 16, 12, 51, 25, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'vinitS101', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 440824888, 'comment_body': "Oh, my bad. I didn't notice this. I'll make the changes asap.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 6, 16, 12, 52, 17, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'vinitS101', 'type': 'User'}]

pr_title: hotkeys: Quote selected text when '>' hotkey is pressed.
pr_body:
Currently, the 'r' hotkey can be used to respond to the selected message.
This commit slightly changes this behavior to quote the selected text, if any, in the response.

[Relevant conversation on CZO](https://chat.zulip.org/#narrow/stream/137-feedback/topic/Quote.20piece.20of.20message.20if.20it.20is.20selected.20when.20clicking.20Reply/near/895456).

Edit:
[Example GIF in a comment below](https://github.com/zulip/zulip/pull/15235#issuecomment-642719790).
pr_review_comments: [{'comment_id': 440194562, 'comment_body': "I don't understand why that's a bad thing. If I select some text, I think that the `>` hotkey makes more sense for quoting the selection and replying.\r\n\r\nIn fact, between `r` and `>`, the later already has quoting behavior so it feels natural to extend that instead of r.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 6, 15, 13, 57, 2, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'aero31aero', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 441007852, 'comment_body': "I've changed the this in my updated commit. The `>` hotkey now triggers this instead of the `r` hotkey.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 6, 16, 17, 5, 26, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'vinitS101', 'type': 'User'}]

pr_title: emojis: Add JS tooltips for emojis in messages.
pr_body:
This replaces the current HTML hover with JS tooltips for both
normal and custom emojis in messages.

Part of Issue #15632.

![msg_emojis_1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/25329595/86517365-fd4e2800-be45-11ea-9beb-0d4b5c8eae68.gif)
pr_review_comments: [{'comment_id': 449797772, 'comment_body': "Having multiple elements with the same id is invalid in HTML since the `id` must be unique, see https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/dom.html#the-id-attribute. So this should probably be a `class` instead. I also find the plural `emojis` unfitting because it's just a single emoji.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 4, 19, 7, 25, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Gittenburg', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 449798164, 'comment_body': 'I think `top` would be a better placement because with `bottom` the tooltip can be partially covered by the mouse cursor.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 4, 19, 14, 14, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Gittenburg', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 449887031, 'comment_body': 'I tested this out with `top`, and it feels a bit funny.  Especially if the message is a one line emoji, as it obstructs the user name.\r\n\r\nI also noticed only a very minor cover of the tooltip (which never covered the actual text) if you hover over the emoji coming up from the bottom.  Otherwise this feels like a non-issue.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 5, 14, 59, 2, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'whoodes', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 449888598, 'comment_body': 'Might as well get rid of the other unnecessary escape characters in the tests you touched here as well?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 5, 15, 16, 3, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'whoodes', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 449907109, 'comment_body': 'I tested `top` initially, and I also think that `bottom` is better for this.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 5, 18, 47, 48, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'vinitS101', 'type': 'User'}]

pr_title: markdown: Make normal urls and dropbox urls inline.
pr_body:
This change makes all urls inline and removes the image preview for dropbox urls, treating them the same as normal urls.

Follow-up to PR #15773.


**GIFs or Screenshots:** 

![Screenshot_2](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/25329595/87954114-89f51900-cac9-11ea-86ae-32d4ae9785ea.png)
pr_review_comments:
[{'comment_id': 455911689, 'comment_body': 'The `url` parameter can be extracted from `found_url` which would make this function signature cleaner.

```py
(url, text) = found_url.result
yt_id = self.youtube_id(url)
```

', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 16, 16, 21, 49, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'aero31aero', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 455912245, 'comment_body': "What's bugging me about this code is that `youtube` is actually `youtube_thumbnail_image` or something, this variable name is misleading. Maybe we can use `yt_image` here keeping it in line with `yt_id`.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 16, 16, 22, 41, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'aero31aero', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 455912349, 'comment_body': "Got it. I'll make the change.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 16, 16, 22, 53, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'vinitS101', 'type': 'User'}]

pr_title: compose: Update compose placeholder text if recipients are changed.
pr_body:
The placeholder text is now updated every time recipients of Private Messages are changed (added or removed).

Fixes #15897.

**GIFs or Screenshots:** 

For PMs:

![compose_placeholder_group_pms](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/25329595/88553993-90444180-d043-11ea-896f-251d328ea614.gif)

![compose_placeholder_streams_fixed](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/25329595/88933754-71d98280-d29d-11ea-800f-574805165f6c.gif)
